  "text" : {
    "status" : "generated",
    "div" : "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h2>RR23-Umbrella Measure.</h2><ul><li>Purpose: proportional measure, proportion of patients who were injured due to rockfall, and who received a tiny umbrella within 7 days after the date of diagnosis.</li><li>Initial population: Patients aged 16 and older who have sustained an injury due to falling rock.</li><li>Denominator: Initial Population</li><li>Numerator: Supply of 'ACME Umbrella' within 7 days of 'recording of the (latestmost recent) rock fall condition within the measurement period'.</li></ul>  </div>"
